{"questionId":"9066403","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Rhenium, Re, was the last element with a stable isotope to be isolated.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The stable isotope of rhenium contains 110 neutrons.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">State the nuclear symbol notation&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{\\text{Z}}^{\\text{A}}{\\text{X}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>Z</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>A</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>X</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> for this isotope.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{{\\text{75}}}^{{\\text{185}}}{\\text{Re}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>75</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>185</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>Re</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066403","referenceCode":"19M.2.hl.TZ2.a","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The stable isotope of rhenium contains 110 neutrons. State the nuclear symbol notation Z A X for this isotope.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 2: Atomic structure","2.1 The nuclear atom","Core","Topic 2: Atomic structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}